&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Marketing Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mural Health is a fast-growing clinical technology start-up that makes clinical trials easier for participants.&amp;nbsp; Our mission is to eliminate any barriers participants or caregivers experience while being part of a clinical trial. Mural Health is looking to expand our team with a Product Marketing Manager.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are you?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Product Marketing Manager to own how Mural Health shows up in the market. This role sits at the intersection of product, sales, and marketing - translating platform capabilities into clear, compelling narratives that resonate with sophisticated stakeholders in the clinical trials and life science space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll define our positioning, arm our sales team to win, and lead go-to-market execution for product launches. You&#39;ll be both the strategist and the executor - setting direction and producing the materials that bring it to life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Remote US&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports To: &lt;/strong&gt;Chief Commercial Officer and works in close collaboration with Sales, Product, and the broader Marketing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own positioning and client-facing content for new product launches and existing offerings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead go-to-market execution for product releases and feature launches — from strategy through external communication to internal enablement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor the competitive landscape and market trends, synthesizing findings into actionable insights for sales and leadership, and ensuring messaging and positioning remains current as the market and product evolve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally to translate product capabilities into clear differentiators and value for our customers, and enable the commercial team to communicate those effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the voice of the customer internally — incorporating feedback from customers and users to continuously iterate on messaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain sales materials across pitch decks, one-pagers, ROI frameworks, and commercial talk tracks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have at least 4 years of experience in product marketing, ideally at a B2B SaaS company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have driven new product launches and feature releases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a strong writer who can quickly learn technical products and translate them into clear, relevant narratives for non-technical audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You thrive in a lean environment where you set strategy and get to execute it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You enjoy cross-functional collaboration to drive alignment across product, sales, and marketing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are an effective project manager, able to juggle multiple priorities and communicate progress clearly across internal stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are comfortable using AI and other tools to accelerate research, content creation, and competitive analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
